<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042318840">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165042318842">
<p id="fs-id1165042318844">What additional restrictions are necessary on the function <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>?</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi><mo>?</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165042350211">
<p id="fs-id1165042350213">We need <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mi>f</mi></annotation-xml></semantics></math> to be twice continuously differentiable.</p>
</div>
</div>
