<p id="fs-id1165042332049">The following two exercises consider a bank investment. The initial investment is <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>10,000</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>10,000</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> After <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>25</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mn>25</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> years, the investment has tripled to <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>30,000</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>30,000</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165042710933">
